English: Letter in a Bottle
Indonesian: Letter in a Bottle

English: Hello adventurer... would you bring me $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Atrox? I want to build giant wings I can soar the skies with! Bring me all you can find...
Indonesian: Halo petualang... maukah kamu membawakanku $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Atrox? Aku ingin membangun sayap raksasa yang bisa digunakan untuk terbang! Bawakan aku semua yang bisa kamu temukan...

English: Tigars are known to have some of the strongest teeth in all of Madrigal. If you come across $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ could you bring me a few? I'm crafting a giant dagger... it'll be HUGE!
Indonesian: Tigars diketahui memiliki gigi terkuat di seluruh Madrigal. Jika kamu menemukan $QUEST_END ITEM_NAME$ bisakah kamu membawakan beberapa? Aku sedang membuat belati raksasa... itu akan menjadi BESAR!

English: The glass inside a Meral's $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ can enhance a person's vision thrice their normal spotting distance. Collect me enough and I could build a telescope to peer halfway across the globe!
Indonesian: Kaca di dalam Meral $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dapat meningkatkan penglihatan seseorang tiga kali lipat jarak penglihatan normalnya. Kumpulkan secukupnya dan aku bisa membuat teleskop untuk mengintip belahan dunia!

English: All this inventing has me famished! Could you go get me some of the Kingster's $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$? We'll eat like kings! Don't worry, I'll share...
Indonesian: Semua penemuan ini membuatku kelaparan! Bisakah kamu membelikanku beberapa Kingster $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$? Kami akan makan seperti raja! Jangan khawatir, aku akan berbagi...

English: After all that seafood I couldn't eat another bite! For this next invention, I need $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the large crabs called Creper. From their hard carapace I will craft the strongest of armors. I forsee a fate in which doning this armor will save Coral Island!
Indonesian: Setelah semua makanan laut itu, aku tidak bisa makan lagi! Untuk penemuan berikutnya, aku memerlukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari kepiting besar bernama Creper. Dari karapasnya yang keras aku akan membuat baju zirah yang paling kuat. Aku meramalkan nasib di mana mengenakan baju besi ini akan menyelamatkan Coral Island!

English: The Naga are powerful warriors of the sea... their $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ are said to hold magical powers that can be used to harness purple energy. I have a healthy fear of Purple Magic, but what doesn't kill you only makes you stronger.
Indonesian: Naga adalah pejuang laut yang kuat... mereka $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dikatakan memiliki kekuatan magis yang dapat digunakan untuk memanfaatkan energi ungu. Aku punya ketakutan yang sehat terhadap Purple Magic, tapi apa yang tidak membunuhmu hanya akan membuatmu lebih kuat.

English: The Dorian have risen from the seas around our island! Please defeat them and collect their $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ as proof. My inventions can only hold them back for so long...
Indonesian: Dorian telah muncul dari lautan di sekitar pulau kami! Silakan kalahkan mereka dan kumpulkan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ mereka sebagai bukti. Penemuanku hanya bisa menahannya begitu lama...

English: The $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ of the Okean must be mine! I know having their crown won't make me a king, but it will put me on the path of my dream. To be King of Coral Island!
Indonesian: $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Okean harus menjadi milikku! Aku tahu memiliki mahkota mereka tidak akan menjadikanku seorang raja, tapi itu akan menempatkanku pada jalur impianku. Menjadi King of Coral Island!

English: With the $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kraken, I could finally write to all my friends across the oceans. There's never enough time to keep up with everyone...
Indonesian: Dengan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Kraken, aku akhirnya bisa menulis surat kepada semua teman di seberang lautan. Tidak pernah ada cukup waktu untuk mengikuti semua orang...

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any of the Atrox crawling around the island.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Atrox mana pun yang merayapi pulau.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Tigars around the island.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Tigars di sekitar pulau.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Meral patroling the beaches.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Meral yang berpatroli di pantai.

English: You may find delicious $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Kingsters in shallow waters around the island.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ lezat dari Kingsters di perairan dangkal sekitar pulau.

English: You may find tough $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Creper around the beach area.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ yang sulit dari Creper di sekitar area pantai.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Naga around Coral Island.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ dari Naga di sekitar Coral Island.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ left behind by Dorian around Coral Island.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ yang ditinggalkan oleh Dorian di sekitar Coral Island.

English: You may find magnificient $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Okean, deep in the waters of Coral Island's seas.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ yang menakjubkan dari Okean, jauh di perairan Coral Island.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ inside the bellies of the deep-sea Kraken.
Indonesian: Kamu mungkin menemukan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ di perut laut dalam Kraken.

English: Please, don't make me go collect $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ all on my own... I'm too busy dreaming up new inventions!
Indonesian: Tolong, jangan paksa aku mengumpulkan $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ sendirian... Aku terlalu sibuk memimpikan penemuan baru!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll be soaring the skies with ease. See you at the Rainbow Race!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Sebentar lagi aku akan terbang ke angkasa dengan mudah. Sampai jumpa di Rainbow Race!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll have the biggest dagger in Madrigal. Hehehe, catch me showing off to the Demians!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Sebentar lagi aku akan mendapatkan belati terbesar di Madrigal. Hehehe, tangkap aku pamer ke Demian!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll be able to see the sights without ever leaving my home!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Sebentar lagi aku akan bisa melihat pemandangan tanpa harus meninggalkan rumah!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! We're going to be so full! Eat up, it's time to feast!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Kami akan sangat kenyang! Makanlah, saatnya berpesta!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll have armor enough to defend Coral Island against all evil!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Sebentar lagi aku akan punya baju besi yang cukup untuk mempertahankan Coral Island dari segala kejahatan!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll know more about this Purple Magic... Perhaps one day enough to stop its evil from taking over Coral Island.
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Saya akan segera mengetahui lebih banyak tentang Purple Magic ini... Mungkin suatu hari cukup untuk menghentikan kejahatannya mengambil alih Coral Island.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Those fishy creatures have a strange power that makes them age slower than others. Perhaps studying their teeth can give us insight to the Dorian's special powers.
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Makhluk mencurigakan tersebut memiliki kekuatan aneh yang membuat mereka menua lebih lambat dibandingkan makhluk lain. Mungkin mempelajari gigi mereka dapat memberi kita wawasan tentang kekuatan khusus Dorian.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! It's just a dream... but I hope to one day greet you again as King of Coral Island.
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Itu hanya mimpi... tapi aku berharap suatu hari nanti bisa menyambutmu lagi sebagai King of Coral Island.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! I've decided to write these letters and deliver them myself. Thank you for everything... I hope to see you again one day!
Indonesian: Terima kasih telah mengumpulkan semua $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu, petualang! Aku telah memutuskan untuk menulis surat-surat ini dan mengirimkannya sendiri. Terima kasih atas segalanya... Aku berharap dapat bertemu kamu lagi suatu hari nanti!

English: That isn't nearly enough $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ for me to build one of my grand inventions... come back with more!
Indonesian: $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ itu tidak cukup bagiku untuk membuat salah satu penemuan hebat... kembalilah dengan lebih banyak lagi!

English: $QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ cackles with glee! Soon their inventions will become a reality.
Indonesian: $QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ tertawa gembira! Penemuan mereka akan segera menjadi kenyataan.

English: The Skulls of the Hundur Sharpfoot
Indonesian: The Skulls of the Hundur Sharpfoot

English: The Hundur Sharpfoot gather near Kaillun’s borders, and their skulls bear strange markings. The Muran need them to decipher the secrets behind their rituals.
Indonesian: The Hundur Sharpfoot gather near Kaillun’s borders, and their skulls bear strange markings. The Muran need them to decipher the secrets behind their rituals.

English: Excellent! The Muran are counting on you. Go gather 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ and return once you have enough. You can find them on the Hundur Sharpfoot.
Indonesian: Excellent! The Muran are counting on you. Go gather 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ and return once you have enough. You can find them on the Hundur Sharpfoot.

English: I see… but these creatures are growing more aggressive. Come back if you change your mind.
Indonesian: I see… but these creatures are growing more aggressive. Come back if you change your mind.

English: You haven't gathered enough skulls yet… Keep going, each specimen is important to us.
Indonesian: You haven't gathered enough skulls yet… Keep going, each specimen is important to us.

English: Perfect! These skulls will be of great use to us. Kaillun thanks you for your determination.
Indonesian: Perfect! These skulls will be of great use to us. Kaillun thanks you for your determination.

English: The Skulls of the Samoset
Indonesian: The Skulls of the Samoset

English: The Samoset spirits have grown increasingly aggressive in the plains. The sages of Kaillun seek their skulls to understand the source of their unusual unrest.
Indonesian: The Samoset spirits have grown increasingly aggressive in the plains. The sages of Kaillun seek their skulls to understand the source of their unusual unrest.

English: Thank you! The Samoset spirits are becoming unstable. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Samoset so we can analyze their unrest.
Indonesian: Thank you! The Samoset spirits are becoming unstable. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Samoset so we can analyze their unrest.

English: Very well… but their unrest intensifies each day. Return if you change your mind.
Indonesian: Very well… but their unrest intensifies each day. Return if you change your mind.

English: You still don't have enough… Keep going, we must understand what's disturbing them.
Indonesian: You still don't have enough… Keep going, we must understand what's disturbing them.

English: Perfect! These skulls will help us uncover the truth. Thank you for your help.
Indonesian: Perfect! These skulls will help us uncover the truth. Thank you for your help.

English: The Claws of the Kyouchish
Indonesian: The Claws of the Kyouchish

English: The Kyouchish have been injuring many Muran scouts with their corrosive strikes. Their claws are needed to craft a protective remedy.
Indonesian: The Kyouchish have been injuring many Muran scouts with their corrosive strikes. Their claws are needed to craft a protective remedy.

English: Good! Their claws are poisoning our scouts. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kyouchish.
Indonesian: Good! Their claws are poisoning our scouts. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kyouchish.

English: I understand… but we're running out of remedies. Return if you wish to help.
Indonesian: I understand… but we're running out of remedies. Return if you wish to help.

English: You're still missing some. The Kyouchish are dangerous, stay careful.
Indonesian: You're still missing some. The Kyouchish are dangerous, stay careful.

English: Excellent! With these claws, our healers can prepare a proper antidote.
Indonesian: Excellent! With these claws, our healers can prepare a proper antidote.

English: The Kanonicus Antidote
Indonesian: The Kanonicus Antidote

English: The Kanonicus carry a natural antidote within their dorsal glands. Kaillun urgently needs it to heal warriors poisoned by the Lycans.
Indonesian: The Kanonicus carry a natural antidote within their dorsal glands. Kaillun urgently needs it to heal warriors poisoned by the Lycans.

English: Thank you! Their natural antidote is vital for our wounded soldiers. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kanonicus.
Indonesian: Thank you! Their natural antidote is vital for our wounded soldiers. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kanonicus.

English: A shame… several warriors are still waiting to be treated.
Indonesian: A shame… several warriors are still waiting to be treated.

English: You don’t have enough yet. Hurry, every drop counts.
Indonesian: You don’t have enough yet. Hurry, every drop counts.

English: Perfect! Thanks to you, we can finally treat our wounded.
Indonesian: Perfect! Thanks to you, we can finally treat our wounded.

English: The Magic Skulls of the Redcloud
Indonesian: The Magic Skulls of the Redcloud

English: The Redcloud generate a mysterious energy within their skulls. Muran shamans want to study this magic to reinforce the city's protective wards.
Indonesian: The Redcloud generate a mysterious energy within their skulls. Muran shamans want to study this magic to reinforce the city's protective wards.

English: Very well! Their skulls contain a mysterious energy. We must study it. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Redcloud.
Indonesian: Very well! Their skulls contain a mysterious energy. We must study it. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Redcloud.

English: Alright… but this magic could strengthen our defenses.
Indonesian: Alright… but this magic could strengthen our defenses.

English: You don’t have enough energy-charged skulls yet. Keep going!
Indonesian: You don’t have enough energy-charged skulls yet. Keep going!

English: Excellent work! These skulls are a true source of power.
Indonesian: Excellent work! These skulls are a true source of power.

English: The Devil’s Teeth
Indonesian: The Devil’s Teeth

English: A strange corruption spreads through Kaillun as Devil Spirits multiply. Their teeth contain a demonic essence the sages wish to seal away.
Indonesian: A strange corruption spreads through Kaillun as Devil Spirits multiply. Their teeth contain a demonic essence the sages wish to seal away.

English: Be brave! The Devil Spirits are growing in number. Their teeth must be sealed. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Devil Spirits.
Indonesian: Be brave! The Devil Spirits are growing in number. Their teeth must be sealed. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Devil Spirits.

English: I understand… but their influence spreads further each night. Return carefully.
Indonesian: I understand… but their influence spreads further each night. Return carefully.

English: Not enough teeth to contain the demonic energy yet. Keep gathering.
Indonesian: Not enough teeth to contain the demonic energy yet. Keep gathering.

English: Very good! These teeth will be purified and neutralized. You’ve done us a great service.
Indonesian: Very good! These teeth will be purified and neutralized. You’ve done us a great service.

English: The Bloodstained Fangs of the Hellhound
Indonesian: The Bloodstained Fangs of the Hellhound

English: Hellhounds roam dangerously close to Kaillun, and their bloodied fangs leave lingering wounds. The Muran need them to forge weapons capable of driving these beasts back.
Indonesian: Hellhounds roam dangerously close to Kaillun, and their bloodied fangs leave lingering wounds. The Muran need them to forge weapons capable of driving these beasts back.

English: Perfect! Their blood-soaked fangs are deadly. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Hellhounds to us for forging.
Indonesian: Perfect! Their blood-soaked fangs are deadly. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Hellhounds to us for forging.

English: Very well… but the Hellhounds still lurk around Kaillun.
Indonesian: Very well… but the Hellhounds still lurk around Kaillun.

English: You don’t have enough. Their fangs are essential to forge weapons that can repel them.
